From Henry Spencer Subject Re temperature of the dark sky In article C E G KM Tom Van Flandern writes the temperature of the night sky as seen from space You'll find that in Allen, C W , Astrophysical Quantities , Athlone Press, Dover, NH, rd edition, pp I have a copy of Allen, and it never occurred to me to look in there I must be getting old I'll look it up when I get home Thanks the temperature is degrees K I'd remembered a rather higher number, but that may have been for the lunar nearside, where the Earth is a significant heat source SVR resembles a high speed collision Henry Spencer U of Toronto Zoology between SVR and SunOS Dick Dunn utzoo henry